Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @parsnips{6%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Slice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(half)(peeled and minced). Strip @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have ½ tsp (1 tsp for 4).

> TIP: If you have any extra rosemary sprigs, save them for an easy garnish!

Toss parsnips and carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Toss potatoes on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast parsnips and carrots on top rack and potatoes on middle rack.)

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, @dried thyme{½%tsp} (¾ tsp for 4 servings), salt, and pepper.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

In same pan, melt @butter{1%tbsp} over medium heat. Add reserved shallot and cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a drizzle of oil, @flour{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of thyme; cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Whisk in @water{1%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and @salt{¼%tsp}. (For 4, use 2 cups of water and ½ tsp salt.) Bring to a simmer, whisking constantly, until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> Use pan used for chicken or beef here.

Remove from heat; stir in @cream cheese{2%tbsp} until thoroughly combined. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Melt @butter{2%tbsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring frequently, until butter is foamy and flecked with amber brown bits, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in rosemary. Carefully transfer rosemary brown butter to a #medium bowl{}.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Add carrots and parsnips to bowl with rosemary brown butter; toss to coat.

Divide chicken, carrots and parsnips, and potatoes between plates. Spoon gravy over chicken and serve.

> Slice chicken or beef against the grain.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.